condition.narrative: Environmental and Social Commitment Plan, ESS 1, 1.1 ORGANIZATIONAL STRUCTURE The PIU will hire one full-time specialist, withterms of reference acceptable to the Association, who will be responsible for all environmental and social aspects of the Project.The GF will hire two (part-time) consultants, one environmental and one social, with terms of reference acceptable to theAssociation. These specialists shall be hired as soon as possible and not later than within four months of the effectiveness dateof the Additional Financing and shall be maintained throughout Project implementation. Prior to their appointment, seniormanagement at both the PIU and GF will be assigned responsibility for ensuring compliance with the ESCP and relevant ESSes.

Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I.A.1The Recipient shall maintain during Project implementation, a Steering Committee tooversee the Project and serve as the highest-level consultative and decision-making body, responsible for strategic guidance,coordination, and implementation support.

Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I.A.2The Recipient shall maintain, at all times during Project implementation, theProject Implementation Unit (“PIU”), with functions and responsibilities acceptable to the Association as set forth in the ProjectOperational Manual (“POM”), including, inter alia, the responsibility to coordinate, manage, implement, monitor and supervise thecarrying out of the Project.

Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I.B.1The Recipient, through MOF, shall amend the Project Operational Manual, not laterthan thirty (30) days after Effective Date, in a manner satisfactory to the Association, and shall ensure that the Project iscarried out in accordance with the POM, setting forth rules, methods, guidelines, and procedures for the carrying out of theProject.

Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I.B.2The Recipient, through MOF, shall amend the RFA Procedural Manual, in a mannersatisfactory to the Association, and shall ensure that Part 1 of the Project is carried out in accordance with the RFA ProceduralManual, setting forth rules, methods, guidelines, and procedures for the carrying out Part 1 of the Project

Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I.B.3The Recipient, through MOF, shall amend the PRSF Procedural Manual, in a mannersatisfactory to the Association, and shall ensure that Part 2 of the Project is carried out in accordance with the PRSF ProceduralManual, setting forth rules, methods, guidelines, and procedures for the carrying out Part 2 of the Project

For purposes of carrying out Part 1 of the Project, the Recipient, through PIU, shall cause each Selected DisbursementAdministrator (“SDA”), pursuant to an agreement (“SDA Agreement”) satisfactory to the Association, to provide concessionalfinancing (“Reimbursable Financial Assistance” or “RFA”) to the pertinent Eligible MSME in accordance with the eligibility criteriaand procedures set forth in the RFA Procedural Manual and pursuant to the pertinent RFA Agreement.

For the implementation of Part 2.1 of the Project and prior of commencement of implementation of said activities under Part 2.1 ofthe Project, the Recipient, through MOF, shall:(a) make available the Financing proceeds allocated to Category (2), into a newaccount opened for the purpose to provide Portfolio Partial Credit Guarantees (“PRSF Account”) to Eligible PFIs under PRSF on termsand conditions acceptable to the Association and further described in the PRSF Procedural Manual; and (b) enter into an agreementwith State Guarantee Fund (“SGF”) for purposes of delegating certain implementation functions related to the administration of PRSFAccount and the PRSF (“SGF Agent Agreement”), on terms and conditions acceptable to the Association and further detailed in thePRSF Procedural Manual.

The Recipient has installed, not later than 30 days after Effective Date, an automated accounting software in accordance with theRecipient’s accounting and reporting requirements and satisfactory to the Association.

The Recipient shall establish not later than 2 months from the Effective Date and, thereafter maintain during Projectimplementation, a Steering Committee to oversee the Project and serve as the highest-level consultative and decision-making body,responsible for strategic guidance, coordination, and implementation support.

The Recipient shall maintain, at all times during Project implementation, the Project Implementation Unit (“PIU”), with functionsand responsibilities acceptable to the Association as set forth in the Project Operational Manual (“POM”), including, inter alia,the responsibility to coordinate, manage, implement, monitor and supervise the carrying out of the Project
